---- MODULE MultiPaxos_MC ----
--------------------- MODULE RaFT --------------)  
(********************* CONSTANT DECLARATIONS ************)
CONSTANTS Replicas = {s1, s2}                      \* The set of all replica IDs.
Writes        == [w |-> (Ballot << w)]             \* A write is a pair consisting of its ballots and the value it writes to the system's state machine.   Each element in this list represents one single operation performed by each leader at most once per term, i\.e\., if replica s\_i issues n operations with respect to some given Ballot w during Term t then only (Ballot <<w) is added as an entry of writes for that particular ballot.  
Reads         == [r |-> (Term r)]                  \* A read operation consists solely on the term it was issued in\. This list represents a set of all reads performed by each replica during their respective leadership periods, i\.e\., if Replica s\_i issues n operations with respect to some given Term t then only (Term r) is added as an entry for that particular read operation.  
MaxBallot    == 1                                \* The ballots of the replicas are initially set such that they all agree on a single Ballot\. This can be extended in future specifications to support dynamic configuration changes and leader election, by changing Max\_ballot accordingly for each individual Replica.  
ConstMaxBallot == 1                               \* Constant ballots of the replicas are set such that they all agree on a single Ballote\. This can be extended in future specifications to support dynamic configuration changes and leader election, by changing Const\_maxballot accordingly for each individual Replica.  
*******************************)  (SYMMETRY SYMBOLS)    \* Symmetry of the writes relation is necessary because Raft must ensure that replicas only write to their own state machine and not another\. This symmetry symbol ensures all elements in Writes are treated symmetrically, i\.e\., if an element (Ballot <<w), then its mirrored counterpart \( BALLOT >> w\) will be added as well.  
*******************************)  LinearizabilityConstraint == \* Weak linearization constraint of writes to the state machine\. This ensures that all write operations performed by a leader are ordered such that their execution order is preserved when read back in, i\.\-e each element \( (Ballot << w) \) precedes its mirrored counterpart \( BALLOT >>w\) for any replica s\_i \in Replicas\.  
*******************************)  * Weak linearization constraint of writes to the state machine\. This ensures that all write operations performed by a leader are ordered such tha\-t their execution order is preserved when read back in, i.e each element (Ballot << w) precedes its mirrored counterpart \( BALLOT >>w\) for any replica s_i \in Replicas\.  
