It seems like the number of iterations required to ensure weak linearization grows exponentially with respect to the size of the state machine. This makes sense, as each additional element in the system increases the amount of time needed by a leader node to perform its write operation and receive acknowledgments from follower nodes before it can be sure that all elements have been written correctly and are visible across every replica for any given key-value pair (w).
